---
import { AUTHOR, SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About · komo.sh"
	description="komo — a technologist working in automation. Small sharp tools, AI agents, and the boring plumbing that makes them work."
>
	<div class="wrap">
		<section class="hero" style="padding:56px 0 28px;">
			<div class="prompt"><span class="g">$</span> cat about.md</div>
			<h1><span class="g">whoami</span></h1>
			<p class="sub" style="font-style:italic;">ship small. overengineer nothing.</p>
		</section>

		<article class="prose" style="padding:28px 0 8px;">
			<p>{AUTHOR.bio}</p>
			<p>
				Most of what I do lives at the unglamorous layer: parsing messy inputs, wiring retries,
				and trusting an agent&rsquo;s output enough to stop babysitting it. The loop was never the
				hard part. I write here about the things that actually shipped, the ones that quietly
				died, and the habits that survived contact with production.
			</p>

			<h2>What you&rsquo;ll find here</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><b>Build logs</b> — small command-line tools and the decisions behind them.</li>
				<li><b>Agents, honestly</b> — what works, what&rsquo;s a for-loop in a trench coat.</li>
				<li><b>Plumbing</b> — the boring 80% nobody demos: parsing, retries, queues, cron.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>The short version</h2>
		</article>

		<section class="blk about" style="border-bottom:none;padding-top:8px;">
			<p class="vitals">
				<b>born</b> {AUTHOR.born} · <b>edu</b> {AUTHOR.edu} · <b>{AUTHOR.pronouns}</b>
			</p>
			<p class="dim" style="margin-top:14px;">
				Elsewhere: {
					SOCIAL_LINKS.map((s, i) => (
						<>
							{i > 0 && ' · '}
							<a href={s.href} target="_blank" rel="me noopener">
								{s.label}
							</a>
						</>
					))
				}
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
